apollo 18 is a 2011 american-canadian alternate history found footage science fiction horror film written by brian miller, directed by gonzalo lopez-gallego, and produced by timur bekmambetov and michele wolkoff. after various release date changes, the film was released in the united states, united kingdom, and canada on september 2, 2011. however, the release dates for other territories vary.the film is lopez-gallego is first english-language movie. the film is premise is that the cancelled apollo 18 mission actually landed on the moon in december 1973, but never returned, and as a result the united states has never launched another expedition to the moon. the film is shot in found-footage style, supposedly lost footage of the apollo 18 mission that was only recently discovered.
